      "writtenOn": "2016-04-27T03:19:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m sorry, I wasn\u0027t clear in my response, my bad.\nOld code needed the Align value for a single purpose: to check if the passed buffer is aligned. The new code uses it in one more place:\n char __attribute__((__aligned__(Align))) mArray[StackSize];\nhere it can\u0027t be a constructor parameter, I have to make it a template argument to be compile-time constant.\n\nI\u0027d love to make it ctor argument, it just doesn\u0027t compile.",
      "parentUuid": "48560d47_da5121ca",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 120,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 120,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "ab5856fdec1a89bc416a8b00d4e4715988165390",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
