    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "48560d47_1469a57b",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/shared/OpenglCodecCommon/ProtocolUtils.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 120,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-27T16:19:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah!  I missed that, thanks.\n\n(Though you could declare a max alignment of 8, declare mArray[StackSize+MaxAlign], and have the constructor init a pointer to the properly-aligned interior pointer, so you don\u0027t care about the alignment of mArray.  Not sure it\u0027s better, just pointing out the option.)",
      "parentUuid": "48560d47_c6014c2b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 120,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 120,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "ab5856fdec1a89bc416a8b00d4e4715988165390",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "48560d47_373798a2",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/shared/OpenglCodecCommon/ProtocolUtils.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-27T00:04:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This doesn\u0027t work -- but neither, AFAICT, did the old code.  It works for Align \u003d 1,2,4,8, but not higher -- malloc gives 8-byte alignment.  To do this properly for arbitrary alignments, you need to allocate a buffer whose size is something like \"size + Align - 1\", save the pointer to the start, but have \"get()\" return the interior pointer to the proper alignment.\n\nSame applies to the StackSize case.  You\u0027d need to make mArray larger by Align to ensure you could handle arbitrary alignment.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 130,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "ab5856fdec1a89bc416a8b00d4e4715988165390",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
